<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Inside the Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract, I found the following line:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$this-&gt;_connection-&gt;setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_CASE, PDO::CASE_LOWER);
</code></pre>

<p>Not all the users want attribute case to be lower. Upper and natural are other good choices.
It would be good if attribute case could be one member of the "config" member of the class.
The case type would be removed from the array before building the connection DSN string.
The default value could be PDO::CASE_LOWER, but then the developers would have a better way to change it without having to extend the framework's classes or always call setAttribute before creating a connection.</p>

<p>Important: if this can be done with attribute case, why not define a whole set of PDO attributes upon class construct?</p>

<p>Best regards</p>

